  "texts": [
    "The WordNet-Affect and EmoSenticNet dictionaries performed similarly to some of the CMDs with a lower performance.",
    "EmoSen-ticNet performed the best on this dataset, while the NRC lexicon performed the worst.",
    "Overall, CMDs delivered better performance than RMDs.",
    "There is no clear case of either the statistical significance (Dictionary 2: log-likelihood) or the effect size measure (Dictionary 3: %DIFF) performing better overall.",
    "Rather, we find that the performance varies with the dataset and the pre-processing combination."
